sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K222002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: project of a Mid1 gene disrupted from 489 to 2021 nt
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The gene of that part was one of our negative controls. We have used it to make sure our luminiscent peaks made by our wt strains were not an artifact. We can see the behaviour of that kind of mutant in the grapfic showed below:
[[Image:Graf compar.jpg]]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Angeles Hueso Gil
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes from a deletion of the Mid1 wt gene in Saccharomyces cerevisiae.
